# IPTV Tuner (240-MP Fork)

This repo is a **personal fork of [240-MP](https://github.com/anthonycaccese/240-MP)** used to plan and build an experimental **IPTV Tuner** module that simulates 1990s cable-TV watching (live channels, scrolling TV Guide, CRT-friendly UI).

The module does **not exist yet**. All new work belongs under `modules/iptv_tuner/` (QML) and `src/modules/iptv_tuner/` (C++ backend). Minimize changes to the upstream shell unless required (e.g. a new `manifest.json` setting type for URL fields).

## Stack & dependencies

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| App shell | Qt 6 (Core, Gui, Quick, Qml, Network, Svg), C++17 |
| Playback | **mpv** subprocess via `MpvController` — not libmpv |
| Linux/RPi | libdrm (EGLFS ↔ mpv framebuffer hand-off) |
| Crypto | OpenSSL (Plex only today; IPTV may not need it) |
| Targets | Raspberry Pi 4 (480i CRT / EGLFS), macOS ARM |

Build: see `BUILDING.md`. Run: `APP_ROOT=$(pwd) ./build/240mp`.

