## Roadmap (priority order)

1. M3U playlist + XMLTV EPG integration (**ErsatzTV Legacy first**)
2. Live IPTV channel playback (mpv hand-off)
3. Prevue Channel / TV Guide Channel-inspired guide view
4. Passive scrolling + interactive selection modes
5. Guide theme support (may extend beyond app `color_scheme`)
6. Retro Weather Channel screen (RetroCast or custom template) — optional
7. Remote-control navigation (up/down/left/right/enter/esc only)
8. Analog-style channel transitions
9. Auto-zoom widescreen streams (mpv video-zoom / panscan)

Compatibility with other IPTV sources is **not** a goal until ErsatzTV Legacy works end-to-end.

## Local dev assets (gitignored)

`cursor_dev_files/` is on disk but gitignored. Use it for development:

- `sample_resources/channels.m3u` — ErsatzTV M3U sample
- `sample_resources/xmltv.xml` — ErsatzTV XMLTV sample (~minified single-line XML)
- `visual_inspo/Guide_Channel/` — Prevue / TV Guide visual references
- `visual_inspo/Weather_Channel/` — Weather Channel references

Do not commit private URLs or credentials from samples into the repo.

## Hard constraints

- **Browse & hand-off:** IPTV playback goes through `mpvController.loadAndPlay()` — never embed a video player in QML.
- **Remote-only UI:** No mouse-only interactions; Escape/Backspace exits screens.
- **Responsive sizing:** Use `root.sh` / `root.sw` — never hardcoded pixel sizes.
- **Self-contained module:** Keep IPTV code in `modules/iptv_tuner/` + `src/modules/iptv_tuner/`.
- **No tracking:** Network calls only to the user's configured IPTV server; persist state in the data dir only.
- **Stable settings keys:** Module ID `com.240mp.iptv_tuner`; use `appCore.save_setting` / `get_setting`.

## Planned module registration

When the C++ backend lands, add **one** line in `src/main.cpp` and the `.cpp` in `CMakeLists.txt`:

```cpp
appCore.registerModule("com.240mp.iptv_tuner", "iptvTunerBackend", &iptvTuner, ctx);
```
